cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.AI. 

The paper discusses the use of neural networks for speech recognition and computer vision, which are common topics in the sub-categories of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The focus on the depth of neural networks suggests that cs.NE and cs.LG are the most likely categories, followed by cs.CV and cs.CL, and then cs.AI.
